{"key":"processedPost-9402204","value":{"id":9402204,"first":9399794,"last":9402242,"when":1228878566,"utime":"12/10/08 05:09 AM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><b>billycorgan55 said:</b><br />Is grounded up brown rice and rice flower the same thing? <br /></blockquote><br /><br />No. <br /><br /><a href=\"http://anonym.to/?http://www.rirdc.gov.au/pub/handbook/riceflower.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">Rice flower</a> is an ornamental plant used by flower shops to make decorative flower arrangements.<br /><br />What you want is brown rice <b>flour</b>, which is ground brown rice.&nbsp; Grind it to the consistency of sand.&nbsp; It doesn't need to be ground all the way to a fine powder, although that doesn't seem to hurt.<br />RR","title":"Re: can i grind up brown rice instead of brown rice flower?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}